//!
//! This module is intentionally arch-portable pure logic (bit math + raw
//! physical-address pointer writes), so it is fully unit-testable on the host
//! (`cargo test --lib`) with no QEMU. The kernel wiring (setting `satp`/`PGDL`,
//! enabling translation) lives in the arch modules and consumes the `satp()`
//! value / root physical address produced here.
//!
//! v1 model: a per-run page table that maps the kernel identity (RAM + MMIO,
//! U=0) plus the user buffer linearly at `[USER_BASE, USER_BASE+USER_SIZE)`
//! with U=1. See `.workbench/plans/2026-06-09-user-mmu-paging.md`.
//!
//! Physical addresses are accessed as raw pointers. On the kernel this is valid
//! while translation is OFF during table build (bare mode). On the host test,
//! "physical addresses" are real host pointers into the frame pool, so the same
//! walk logic exercises correctly.

