//! Foreground user-execution run budgets, derived from [`ResourceProfile`].
//!
//! The kernel's no-hang guarantee is that **every foreground user profile runs
//! under a preemptive (timer-bounded) budget** — never `UserRunBudget::unlimited`
//! — so a misclassified CPU loop can always be preempted and the official
//! glibc+musl sequence completes (the completion gate). Previously this was
//! "guaranteed" only by brittle source-string tests that grepped `main.rs` for
//! `UserRunBudget::preemptive(...)`. Here the budgets are CONSTRUCTED from the
//! profile via `const fn`s that can only produce preemptive budgets, and a
//! behavior test asserts the invariant on the real values. `main.rs` derives
//! its budget constants from these, so the invariant is enforced by the type,
//! not by string matching.

